28 @-@ year @-@ old cook found dead in San Francisco Mall
A 28 @-@ year @-@ old chef who recently moved to San Francisco was found dead in the staircase of a local shopping center .
The victim &apos;s brother said that he could not imagine anyone wanting to harm him ; &quot; At last , he was climbing again . &quot;
The body found on Wednesday morning in the Westfield Mall was identified as the 28 @-@ year @-@ old Frank Galicia from San Francisco , informed the forensic department in San Francisco .
The San Francisco Police Department said that death was classified as murder and that the investigation is ongoing .
The victim &apos;s brother , Louis Galicia , told ABS channel KGO in San Francisco that Frank , who had previously worked as a chef in Boston , had obtained his dream job six months ago as a chef at Sons &amp; Daughters Restaurant in San Francisco .
A Sons &amp; Daughters spokesman said they were &quot; shocked and destroyed on the ground &quot; by his death .
&quot; We are a small team that works like a close family and we will sorely miss him , &quot; the speaker continued .
Our thoughts and condolences are with Franks family and friends at this difficult time .
Louis Galicia stated that Frank first lived in hostels , but that &quot; things were finally going up for him . &quot;
&quot; He found an apartment , he had a friend , &quot; Louis Garcia told KGO .
Louis Galicia said he could not imagine anyone wanting to harm his younger brother .
He was a kind person with a big heart .
His way of connecting with his family was to always cook something for us , to prepare dinner for us , &quot; said Louis Galicia .
He never wanted to take part in any kind of confrontation .
He was the brother who floated with the stream .
&quot; In everything that goes wrong in the world , he was that uncut diamond that shone bright every day , &quot; he said .
If you have any information about the case , please call the SFPD &apos;s sign phone at 415 @-@ 575 @-@ 4444 .
