A resident of Banff asked for help in identifying the fish that appeared in his garden in Banff .
Kevin Bain thinks that the 75 fish could be sand eels that were spilt by a spring .
Mr Bain , who lives about 500 metres from the sea , published a video of the spectacle on Periscope in the hope that someone could shed some light on the appearance of the two @-@ inch long fish .
Queensferry Crossing : Bridge now linked to Fife .
The £ 1.35 billion project is due to be completed by May 2017 .
Engineers have linked the north deck of the Queensferry Crossings to the viaduct - meaning that the bridge is now connected to Fife .
It is the first of four &quot; roof blower &quot; closures approaching completion around each of the bridge &apos;s three towers .
The bridge section of Fife is now 600 metres long and weighs 30 000 tonnes .
It has 10,000 tonnes of steel and 20,000 tonnes of concrete as well as 46 inclined cables .
The £ 1.35 billion project is due to be completed by May 2017 .
Economics Minister Keith Brown visited the site today and was one of the first to walk from the land to the bridge .
He said : &apos; This is an historic and symbolic moment in the construction of the Queensferry crossing .
We are all witnesses to a truly epic level of engineering in this project , with over 30,000 tonnes of concrete and steel used for this part of the bridge alone .
Despite the bridge &apos;s massive size and weight , the completion of the closure between the viaduct and bridge bridge end is a delicate activity requiring extremely precise fit tolerances .
In total , almost 79 % of all bridge decks are in their place , and the last section of the deck gets concrete casting for the deck in Rosyth today , which means that the entire deck is ready to be raised to its place on the bridge .
Michael Martin , project manager of Forth Crossing Bridge Constructors , said : &quot; The first closure represents a significant milestone in any bridge project .
In this fantastic project , the shutter represents forward @-@ looking civil engineering and civil engineering .
After installing the last section of the road and connecting it to the northern tower deck under construction , we then had to close the remaining gap on the north or land side .
This was achieved by pulling the northern feeder bridge 700 millimetres south .
This has been a massive and , at the same time , very sensitive activity .
It is massive , because the viaduct is 222 metres long , weighs about 6,000 tonnes and had to be pulled upwards with an incline of about 3 % .
Difficult because the tolerances the team was working towards were tiny - they were only a few millimetres on each side .
Fortunately , everything went very well .
Rescue in Moelfre Bay : Three men are &quot; lucky to be alive . &quot;
Three men are &quot; lucky to be alive &quot; after being thrown by their fishing boat off Anglesey .
The Moelfre RNLI rescue station sounded the alarm on Friday at 13 : 20 BST after a crew was watching the event in Moelfre Bay .
The three men found it difficult to swim safely as their boat moved on by their own efforts .
&quot; We saw the boat turn around near her and imagined the worst , &quot; said the head of the rescue station at Moelfre Vince Jones .
&quot; Fortunately , the strong winds have already blown the boat out of its range by the time we let it go to water , &quot; he added .
Two of the men were rescued by a local fishing boat , while the third man , aged 60 , was exhausted and found hanging on a buoy without a life jacket .
They all came on board the coastal rescue boat and were taken back to the rescue station .
Mr Jones said : &apos; The three men who have been thrown into the water are lucky to be uninjured and alive .
The boat engine had an emergency stop point , but when the boat capsized , it detached itself from the person who was steering the boat .
Someone has watched over these men today .
Serious injury - Man stabs his ex @-@ girlfriend
A man has knifed his ex @-@ girlfriend in Hamburg @-@ Harburg and seriously injured him .
According to the police yesterday , the 50 @-@ year @-@ old had been given the key to the apartment to pick up his personal things .
Instead , the alcoholic perpetrator cut the clothing of his ex @-@ girlfriend .
When she came into the apartment , he stoked on her twice .
The 44 @-@ year @-@ old was injured on the hand and body .
The police were able to arrest the perpetrator .
While the 50 @-@ year @-@ old was destroying his ex @-@ girlfriend &apos;s clothes , he phoned his mother .
She then alerted his sister .
Together with her partner , the 45 @-@ year @-@ old wanted to reassure her brother .
But she could not get him to leave the flat .
That &apos;s why she went out of the house with her partner .
They met the man &apos;s ex @-@ partner on the street .
When the two women entered the flat again , the 50 @-@ year @-@ old pushed his sister to the side and attacked his ex @-@ girlfriend .
Who is building Braunschweig &apos;s affordable apartments ?
The SPD and the Greens believe that investors should be made much more responsible in future .
How do we respond to the bad news that Braunschweig will lose nearly 1300 cheap homes in the next few years ?
The SPD proposes a &quot; concept of action on housing &quot; at the next Council meeting .
But disputes are inevitable .
First and foremost , there is the question of who should actually build the cheap housing .
There is no regulation as yet .
The Chairman of the Socialist Group in the European Parliament , Christoph Bratmann , says : &quot; We agree with the Greens that anyone who wants to build on urban areas must in future designate 20 % of all homes as social housing . &quot;
The low @-@ cost apartments , however , can also be created in existing buildings .
The big point of contention in the town hall , however , according to Bratmann , is : &quot; How to deal with investors who want to build on private land ? &quot;
&quot; We want investors to build at least 10 % , but as many as 20 % , of homes as possible as social housing on such land . &quot;
A new urban housing support programme , which will cost millions and has yet to be funded , is intended to provide incentives .
The problem , says Bratmann : &quot; There is as yet no agreement between the groups . &quot;
The CDU wants to give investors as few rules as possible .
The left wants even tougher conditions for investors .
Despite this , Bratmann said , the housing market is about to get worse .
If the concept of action is implemented , it will create additional tasks in the construction administration .
More staff are needed .
It is unclear whether we will get the professionals .
