By 2020 alone , there will be 500 apartments .
In order to prevent this , planning spokeswoman Nicole Palm argues , ties that are running out should now be purchased by the city .
Consideration would also have to be given to bringing homes back into price fixing .
That is possible in the West City .
At a stroke , the problem could be solved .
In the western city , deadlines expire at the end of the year .
Approximately 1800 apartments could be reclaimed there in the price fixing for low @-@ cost apartments .
The only thing is that the owners , the housing companies , do not want that .
If the number of social housing in the western city were to rise dramatically again , we would be moving away from the goal of so @-@ called mixing .
There will no longer be a concentration of the socially disadvantaged in just a few districts .
The Greens expect there to be further movement in the discussion .
Group chairman Holger Herlitschke says : &quot; For a broad majority , the CDU must be on board . &quot;
It concentrated on more building sites for single family homes .
That does not mean , however , that a compromise cannot be reached after all .
Pokémon Go , a pursuit of health and happiness that pays off .
It is fascinating to watch the world change .
Many people have complained over the last decade that teenagers and children no longer go outside to play , but rather prefer to spend their free time watching television .
Pokemon Go is all about getting people off the sofa and making them more active .
Time on the screen was initially limited to the television , then to video games , and finally to smart phones .
So it is great to see that technology and outdoor activities are not mutually exclusive .
I refer , of course , to the Pokémon Go delusion , an app based on the characters first created for the video games in the 1990s ( later to become a cartoon series , game cards and other spin @-@ offs ) .
Like many pop @-@ culture phenomena , interest fell somewhat before the game was released in the US , Australia , and New Zealand in early July .
The launch in other countries was postponed due to the massive demand that overloaded the servers .
Within days , Pokémon Go had more users than Tinder and almost as many as Twitter .
How does it work ?
In short , players go outside with their smartphones looking for pokémons that can be tracked with a GPS and , once found , &quot; photographed &quot; ( via a screenshot on their mobile phone ) or &quot; captured . &quot;
A generation that played the game when it was younger joined the madness and jumped off the sofa in search of it .
In the US , the game led to a significant increase in the number of steps the &quot; average &quot; person takes every day .
Cardiogram , an Apple Watch app tracking 35,000 users , recently told The Washington Post that within two days of the game &apos;s launch , the number of people tracked each day training for 30 minutes increased from 45 % to 53 % .
The company doesn &apos;t know which of them plays Pokémon Go - it only sees the raw data to improve performance .
Many public education campaigns on health aimed at getting people to &quot; take 30 minutes , &quot; &quot; come off the sofa , &quot; and &quot; be active every day &quot; fell on deaf ears , because many public health messages are boring and come from people who look miserable .
Nevertheless , the importance of sport cannot be overstated .
Those who regularly exercise reduce their chances of developing cancer or depression .
Physical activity helps with weight control , high blood pressure , diabetes , and a long list of benefits that is too long to list here .
But the wonderful thing about Pokémon Go is that it makes people do something in the open air that makes them enjoy it .
Thus , three pillars of health are covered - exercise , fresh air and sunshine , and fun .
Some people even make new friends while hunting .
As always , there are also gruesome spoilers who always have to complain about something .
And yes , someone could walk against a door .
What &apos;s up ?
There has been a breakthrough .
Even if smartphone apps like Fitbit were able to track our activity before , they gave us no reason to play sports as this game does .
What is new will lose its allure and use will wane over time .
As a result of Pokemon &apos;s success , however , there will be more games that combine apps and virtual reality with being active in the real world , helping many people hunt to be more active , fit and healthy .
