How to Protect Krav Maga from Arms Attacks
The world outside is a dangerous place , but this video from Dailymail.com could make it a little safer for you .
We spoke to Rhon Mizrachi , a Grand Master of the Krav Maga Association in New York , to find out how to deal with armed robbers at a close range .
Whether you are approached from the front or the back , this video will show you how to turn the tables on your robber .
When approaching you from behind , the first thing you should do is turn around so that you can see your attacker and &quot; get out of the firing line , &quot; says Mizrachi .
Then grab the gun between your forearm and shoulder before beating it in the face with your free elbow .
Then beat him with his knees into the groin , twisting the weapon out of his hands as the attacker curves with pain , hitting him face with the barrel and moving backwards as they point the gun at him .
For attackers approaching from the front , the technique is similar - move your body out of the firing line , take the gun and twist it so the attacker cannot shoot .
At the same time , shift the weight to the weapon and beat the attacker &apos;s chest , then twist the weapon out of his grip before moving backwards and pointing the weapon at him .
Sounds difficult ?
Watch the video to see exactly how Mizrachi is doing .
But remember that if you are robbed , the safest thing to do is hand over your money - unless you are a Krav Maga grandmaster .
