Sultana was 17 years old and , according to her family , died shortly after she planned to leave the war @-@ torn country and return to England .
&quot; One can only hope that the only good thing is to prevent people from ever making that decision , &quot; Akunjee said , as a warning and warning to others that these are the risks involved in going to a war zone .
In February 2015 , Sultana and two other schoolgirls from eastern London entered Turkey on an airplane , and then on a bus to the Syrian border .
Sultana &apos;s family was told that she had married an ISIS fighter in Syria - and had become a widow in a matter of months .
Reid says that Clinton will remain as Supreme Court candidate in the event of a Garland victory .
Harry Reid , the leader of the Senate Democrats , is convinced that the Democratic presidential candidate , Hillary Clinton , will nominate Judge Merrick Garland for the Supreme Court .
Senate Republicans have blocked Garland &apos;s confirmation since his nomination by Barack Obama in March .
Senate majority leader Mitch McConnell believes that the next president will appoint the late Supreme Court Justice Antonin Scalia &apos;s successor .
Reid said on Thursday during a telephone conference that he expects Clinton to select Garland &quot; with some certainty . &quot;
A Reid spokeswoman later said that he had not yet spoken to Clinton about whether she would nominate Garland and that he was speculating .
He praised Garland , saying that Clinton &apos;s team would not cause trouble with a new candidate .
Garland is the highest court of appeal for the District of Columbia .
Raid said that Republicans blocking Garland &apos;s nomination were lackeys and accomplices to Republican presidential candidate Donald Trump .
He also noted that Donald Trump was unsuitable for the presidency .
