Here comes the Enforcement Trailer .
Germany &apos;s lasers have to adapt to the next generation of speedometers : In several federal states , including Hesse and Brandenburg , new lightning devices are being tested to transfer speed drivers particularly effectively .
The futuristic Enforcement Trailers from Vitronic in Wiesbaden can , for example , be used in accident areas , where it would be too dangerous for mobile measurement by the police .
At motorway construction sites , for example , or bridges with temporary speed limits to be repaired , there is often no necessary infrastructure to ensure compliance with speed limits using a fixed speed camera .
However , a permanent mobile structure can be too dangerous or expensive .
The Enforcement Trailer is self @-@ sufficient : its battery lasts five days in continuous measurement operation , and the case data is transmitted encrypted via a modem .
Laser measuring technology also allows all vehicles to be recorded in multiple lanes at the same time .
Variable speed limits can also be monitored , as well as transit bans by time , lanes and class of vehicle .
According to the manufacturer , when the trailer is in high gear , you can move it with any car with a trailer coupling .
In order to prevent it from simply being stolen , it is lowered in measuring mode , so that the wheels disappear into the armored and , incidentally , shot @-@ proof outer shell .
In addition , a built @-@ in alarm system is supposed to protect the speed camera from vandalism .
According to Vitronic , the trailer has been tested in several federal states since 2015 and is now being used .
Foreign authorities are also flashing with the new technology : France recently ordered 100 pieces , following an order for 150 last year .
