Clarity has been exemplary for 31 years
The managing director of the Water Utility Association &quot; Veitensteingruppe , &quot; Ruppert Göller , retires .
The association is regarded as a &quot; model throughout Bavaria . &quot;
A small Franconian drinking water use association as a model for the big water producers .
Some time ago , this was the original tone of an article on Bavarian radio .
Not long after , the Water Forum honored the Lower Franconia government for its purpose .
The work of the Veitensteingruppe is considered &quot; exemplary throughout Bavaria . &quot;
Behind all this is Rupert Göller , who worked for 31 years in the Zweckverband , including 28 years as Managing Director .
Now he has retired at the age of 65 .
The Drinking Water Utility Association of the Veitenstein Group , based in Kottendorf , Municipality of Breitbrunn , produces around 150,000 cubic metres of water per year and supplies 32 villages and hamlets with around 5500 inhabitants .
Member municipalities are the municipalities of Kirchlauter , Breitbrunn , Lauter , Ebelsbach and the town of Baunach .
There are water supply contracts for other towns and communities .
The current Chairman , Breitbrunn &apos;s Mayor Gertrud Bühl ( FW ) , reminded us that Rupert Göller was appointed water guard in 1985 and was appointed Managing Director of the association as early as 1988 .
&quot; His duties have been very diverse , ranging from water mains construction and maintenance work to office and organisational activities , household planning , charging and contributions to weekend emergency operations , &quot; said the chair .
Outstanding events were the commissioning and inauguration of the new wells ( 1994 ) , the purchase of land in the area of the new wells ( 1998 ) and compensation for farmers , the renovation of the high @-@ altitude reservoirs ( 1999 ) , the purchase of a central computer control system ( 2004 ) and the partial renovation of water pipes .
There has been no standstill and innovations have been introduced time and time again , because water is life and drinking water is the most important food .
In her laudatio she praised Göllers faithful , reliable and correct service for 31 years .
He has put a great deal of effort into his Water Utility Association and he has truly lived the Water Service Association as if it were his own business .
A few weeks ago , as a true practitioner , he had the opportunity to present the Veitenstein Group &apos;s concept for reducing nitrates to the Water Forum in Lower Franconia .
He has received a lot of recognition and praise for that .
Rupert Göller , for his part , praised Water Patron Alfonso Griebel , who worked with him for 28 years .
He is the best water keeper and he was a loyal scarce .
Together we were an unbeatable team .
From his point of view , he described the construction of the well and the restructuring of the functional association as highlights .
The biggest challenge and the most difficult use , however , was the break @-@ up of the pipe at the high container at Kirchlauter on January 3rd .
Here , at minus 17 degrees , we had to work all night to supply the villages with water .
The supply of Neubrunn could also only have been maintained once , because the high @-@ pressure container was filled with hoses from Pettstadt .
The management of the Drinking Water Purpose Association has been handed over to Daniel Stürmer from Lauter , who will succeed Rupert Göller .
