GfK Management steps down after disappointing business figures
GfK , the consumer research company , has replaced its head Matthias Hartmann .
The resignations were sudden - but not entirely surprising .
The difficult situation of the market research company GfK led us to suspect that the longer the promised success is not achieved , the more uncertain CEO Matthias Hartmann &apos;s chair will become .
Turmoil at the head of the Nuremberg @-@ based market research company GfK : Following once again disappointing business figures and the resignation of the company management , the global number five in the sector is facing a new beginning in terms of personnel .
GfK &apos;s CEO plans to leave the company at the end of the year .
The Chairman of the GfK Supervisory Board , Arno Mahert , is already leaving the Supervisory Board with effect from 12 September .
On 1 September , Gerhard Hausruckinger , a former member of the Board of Management , took over the leadership of the company .
He is to officially assume the role of &quot; CEO &quot; until a successor for Hartmann is found .
The company cited &quot; different views &quot; on its long @-@ term business policy orientation as the reason for the resignations .
A company spokesman on Friday did not want to give details .
It is still unclear who will head the market research company in the future .
Investors said on Friday that shareholders were most disappointed by the lack of success of the restructuring that was initiated years ago .
Mr. Hartmann has been at the top of GfK since 2011 .
&quot; The fruits of the restructuring , however , are still not visible after five years , &quot; it said .
Given the latest poor GfK business figures , any shareholder will at some point become restless .
&quot; If this were the case with BMW , the Quandts would do the same , &quot; they said .
The company had been unable to halt its decline in the second quarter of 2016 , following setbacks in the previous quarter .
At € 361.2 million , revenues were down 6.1 percent year @-@ on @-@ year .
Compared with the first half of the year , sales decreased by 3.4 percent to 721.2 million euros .
The profit in the second quarter was mainly impacted by the declining value of the company in view of its difficult economic situation .
All in all , the impairment charges of EUR 139 million that had become necessary in the Consumer Experience division resulted in a loss of EUR 148.2 million for the Group .
In the second quarter of 2015 , GfK had recorded consolidated profits of 19.7 million .
