Students clashed with the police on Thursday in the Brazilian city of Sao Paulo as they gathered to demonstrate against government reforms to the public education system .
The police used tear gas and rubber bullets against the demonstrators .
The trouble began when police officers tried to drive the students apart , causing the police to use rubber bullets and tear gas .
Several hundred students took part in the demonstrations to express their shock at the plans .
According to proposals by the state governor of Sao Paulo Geraldo Alckmin , slightly less than 100 public schools are being closed , while 300,000 students are being implemented to save money .
Some of the protesters could be seen spraying graffiti on walls against interim President Michel Temer .
The recent protests occurred a few days after demonstrators took to the streets en masse to support suspended President Dilma Rousseff , who had been ousted by a Senate vote to remove her from office .
Trade between Russia and Iran soars to 71 % - RT Business
With the lifting of sanctions , Russian Ambassador to Iran Levan Dzhagaryan said that trade between Moscow and Tehran increased by 70.9 % year on year .
Since international sanctions against Iran were lifted , interest on the part of Russian companies in doing business in the country has grown sharply , the Ambassador said .
Russian companies are establishing existing links with Iran , while new firms are ready to gain access to the market .
Of course , further trade expansion is one of the biggest priorities of bilateral cooperation with Iran , &quot; said Dzhagaryan .
He noted that in the first five months of 2016 , Russia @-@ Iran trade turnover increased by 70.9 % compared to the same period in 2015 , and stood at $ 856 million .
In particular , Russian imports to Iran soared by 91.5 % , reaching $ 697 million .
Russian imports from Iran increased by 16 % to $ 158 million .
The upturn in trade was achieved through deliveries of machinery , land vehicles and weapons , &quot; said the Ambassador .
Dzhagaryan expects a record number of Iranian tourists to visit Russia this year .
Last year , Russia &apos;s foreign representation issued about 35,000 visas , primarily travel visas , to Iranian citizens .
Iran also reached the top 20 countries in terms of the number of tourists in Russia .
One could say that the record numbers of Iranian tourists in Russia last year are being broken , &quot; he said .
At the same time , relatively few Russians visit Iran , something that the Ambassador hopes will change .
&quot; Personally , I can recommend visiting the cities of Isfahan , Shiraz and Yazd , which have preserved monuments of ancient Persian civilization in good condition , &quot; he said .
