Olympic 2016 : Chen Xinyi , Silwia Danekova , and Adrian Zielinski are first cases of doping
caught : Due to a positive doping test Adrian Zielinski from Poland is not allowed to take off in Rio .
Rio de Janeiro - The 2016 Olympic Games are overshadowed by the first official cases of doping .
A caught athlete almost won a medal .
Before the seventh day of competition , the first official cases of doping became known at the Olympic Games in Rio de Janeiro .
China &apos;s swimmer Chen Xinyi , Bulgaria &apos;s 3,000 @-@ meter obstacle runner Silwia Danekova , and Poland &apos;s Adrian Zielinski have been tested positively in Brazil and expelled - just before the already @-@ critical athletics competitions begin , these news comes at the wrong time .
In Chen , the diuretic agent hydrochlorothiazide , which is used as a masking agent for doping substances , was discovered as early as last Sunday .
The International Sports Court CAS confirmed on Friday afternoon local time their exclusion from the Olympic Games .
On Sunday , the 18 @-@ year @-@ old had finished fourth in the final over 100 m butterfly , only 0.09 seconds away from the bronze medal .
On Friday , Chen should have participated in the races over 50 m Freistil .
Chen has requested that the International Olympic Committee ( IOC ) open the B sample and hold a hearing .
The National Federation takes the matter &quot; very seriously and requires Chen to cooperate fully in the investigations , &quot; Xinhua quoted in a statement : &quot; We will cooperate with the International Sports Court CAS and will accept the ruling . &quot;
For the first time in history , it is no longer the IOC but the CAS that is responsible for sanctioning athletes with positive cases .
The news of the positive rehearsal at Danekova also trickled through on the night of Rio , and the 33 @-@ year @-@ old went on the offensive herself .
&quot; I had three tests , all negative , and my fourth test was positive , &quot; she told the Bulgarian TV station BNT , &quot; this was an incredible shock . &quot;
She was innocent , &quot; the only explanation could be food supplements , &quot; the athlete explained .
According to the report , the banned substance is EPO , a blood doping drug .
