Better flux of traffic on highway access
The traffic jams regularly on the bypass - here is a picture from November .
But that is about to change : the bending of the law is to be extended .
This is good news for all drivers who find themselves stuck in traffic jams on the surrounding road every evening when they drive over the A43 motorway .
The Landesbetrieb Straßenbau extends next Tuesday and Wednesday ( 16 / 17 August ) in the area between Hammer Straße and the exit Weseler Straße the right turning lane by 700 metres .
Drivers can thread directly from the Hammer Straße to the right .
The big advantage : traffic is divided up earlier , which improves the overall functioning of the busy section of state highway 51 .
The CDU faction in the districts of Münster @-@ West had the idea of extending the exit .
The traffic constriction on the feeder irritates drivers especially between 5 and 7 p.m.
On weekdays , the backlog reaches as far as the bridge over the Albersloh Path and sometimes beyond .
The reason for this is the bottleneck on the B 51 just before the exit Weseler Straße .
From here , traffic is directed only by one lane over the motorway bridge .
The second track had to be dismantled just over three @-@ quarters of a year ago .
The reason : static calculations had shown that the bridge no longer has the necessary load @-@ bearing capacity to accommodate heavy goods traffic in particular by two lanes .
The competent national company cannot say how long this bottleneck and the congestion it will cause on a daily basis will last .
However , years are to be expected : the bridge has an official remaining useful life until 2034 .
For the extension of the right @-@ bending course , the state @-@ run company has deliberately chosen the less congested time during school holidays because of disabilities .
The traffic will pass the construction site in a single lane on Tuesday and Wednesday .
