The international class of the Forest School attended the play &quot; The Invisible House . &quot;
The association Nima &apos;s and the Young Theatre are now planning a music project .
The association Nima &apos;s enables young people from a migrant and refugee background to visit cultural institutions in Münster .
The &quot; Klasse International &quot; of the Waldschule Kinderhaus attended a presentation of the award @-@ winning play &quot; Das unsichtbare Haus &quot; by Young Theater Münster .
In the context of the &quot; Intercultural Journey &quot; initiated by the association Nima &apos;s , 19 students aged between 11 and 15 attended the staging in the Small House .
Since the beginning of the year , the association , which is committed to the cultural integration of young people from a migrant and refugee background , has been offering schools with welcome classes the opportunity to visit cultural institutions in Münster as part of this project .
Most of the class &apos;s young people came to Münster from , among others , Afghanistan , Iran , Serbia , and Syria between September 2015 and March 2016 , and speak little German .
